Three men and a boy died on Monday after two taxis and a car collided in the Western Cape, the provincial health department s emergency services said. Spokesperson Robert Daniels said the accident occurred on the R61, three kilometres outside of Beaufort West. Two minibus taxis and a car collided leaving six more in critical condition, among them another young boy, Daniels said. He said that the six critical patients, together with 13 others also seriously injured but in a stable condition, were rushed to Beaufort West Provincial Hospital by Western Cape Government Health Emergency Medical Services. For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.